  QuestionText: {fileID: 680376254}
  TextQuestions:
  - Have you experienced any problems with your balance or movement?
  - Have you felt any tremors or shaking in your body?
  - Have you experienced tremors or shaking in your hands and arms while at rest?
  - Have you experienced any difficulty in speaking or being understood?
  - Do you have difficulty in swallowing?
  - Do you feel any rigidity or stiffness in your body?
  - Do you have any difficulty in writing, such as smaller and illegible handwriting?
  - Do you have any problems with smiling or blinking?
  - Do you have any trouble sleeping, or do you experience nightmares?
  - Have you observed any decrease in your ability to smell?
  - Have you experienced any trouble with memory or attention?
  - Do you experience constipation problems?
  - Do you have any problems with involuntary or frequent urination?
  - Do you have any problems with walking, such as difficulty initiating or continuing
    movement?
  - Have you experienced urinary retention?
  - Have you experienced freezing while walking?
  - Have you fallen while walking?
  - Do you have visual or auditory hallucinations?
  - If you have Parkinson's disease, do you experience excessive or abnormal movements
    after taking medication?
  - Have you experienced any changes in mood, such as feeling depressed or upset?
  - Have you exhibited any abnormal behavior, such as collecting items excessively?
  - Have you had an increased tendency to buy items excessively?
